===Etymology===

First used by U.S. President Ronald Reagan to describe weak enemies fighting individually or in small, underground groups for their homeland in the Middle East, particularly Palestinians.  Previously, a guerilla, or revolutionary, engaged in guerilla warfare.

===Noun===
# Someone, or a unique group of any size, in a violent power struggle who does not directly engage a superior force in a formal or traditional battle but attacks an Achilles' heal for maximum damage at minimum cost.  Does not apply to superior forces engaged in the same activity.  

# Someone who uses terror as a weapon in a (usually violent) political struggle, typically in an attempt to coerce a more powerful opponent, such as a government.  

